{"type":"message","id":"e8123ef0","parentId":"2438c241","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:02:51.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The drift-chamber repo only has one commit. The SPARK API source files were never committed to git. The `.pyc` files are bytecode but the source is gone.\n\nLooking at the context from the workspace session (CONTEXT.md in the spark project), it says:\n- \"SPARK / Drift Chamber: 🚀 API shipped — FastAPI server built at spark/api/main.py. Ollama on Paperspace = URL unknown (machine may be off).\"\n\nSo the API was \"shipped\" and the code was written, but it was never committed to git. The `.pyc` files are the only compiled remnants.\n\nThis is a real problem. We need to either:\n\n\n1. Decompile the `.pyc` files to recover the source\n2. Rewrite the API from scratch based on what we know it does\n\nThe `.pyc` files in the spark project are in `__pycache__` directories under `api/` and `drift_chamber/`, and since they're bytecode, I could try decompiling them with a tool like `uncompyle6`. But first, let me verify which Python version generated them so I can use the right decompilation approach.\n\nLooking at the file names, I see `cpython-312` and `cpython-314`, which means they were compiled with Python 3.12 and 3.14 respectively. The `api/main.cpython-314.pyc` and `core/engine.cpython-314.pyc` files might be the most critical ones to attempt decompiling, though with Python 3.14 being so new, decompilation support might be limited or non-existent.","thinkingSignature":"ad471d863781acf0f6abe46efd55fc94f1ec7b53e01d73c7c7d09c7feff9c26a"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe API source files were **never committed to git** — they only existed as loose files and are now gone. The `.pyc` bytecode is all that remains. Let me try to decompile them:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3knclea08gev_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip show uncompyle6 pycdc 2>$null; python --version"}}],"api":"anthropic-mes