{"type":"message","id":"026f8476","parentId":"a73f9040","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:00.655Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to rebuild the SPARK API. Let me write the files based on what I know from the bytecode archaeology. I'll need to:\n\n1. `core/concept_universe.py` - CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, ALL_CONCEPTS, DOMAIN_CONCEPTS, numpy operations\n2. `core/thematic_graph.py` - build_thematic_graph, build_creative_concept_universe, CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS, WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT, CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n3. `core/engine.py` - drift_cycle, decay, ConceptGraph, ConceptNode, DriftChamberConfig, imports from drift_chamber\n\n\n4. `core/llm_mapper.py` - OpenAI + Anthropic, build_tension_narrative, sample_drift_path, CREATIVE_TENSIONS, SPARK_VOICE, SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE, SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE\n5. `api/routes/creative.py` - APIRouter, /generate and /expand endpoints, rate limiting, pydantic models\n6. `api/main.py` - FastAPI app, CORS, rate limiting, health and list_plans routes\n\nI'll write these files and also create the data files with CONCEPT_CLUSTERS and CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS.\n\nNow I'm figuring out the directory structure - there's a spark project with drift_chamber as a subdirectory, and engine.py imports from drift_chamber as a package. I need to make sure the path setup is correct so those imports work properly.\n\nFor the concept clusters, I can see from the session context that there are 9 human-designed clusters with 35,778 adjacencies across 217 concepts. The key tensions driving the narrative are likely things like chaos versus order, memory versus forgetting, and other thematic oppositions that shape the drift chamber's behavior.\n\nI'll start building out the implementation files in order: concept_universe, thematic_graph, engine, llm_mapper, the creative route, and main. For the concept clusters themselves, I'll create nine groupings that map to the 35,778 adjacency structure—things like emotions, abstract reasoning, time, perception, creativity, biological systems, physical space, and social structures—each with their own set of concepts that interconnect within and across clusters.","thinkingSignature":"f0b31ed54f4e125b35a936eb3bf5ff99d532e0f93389230537b13a9d6b0ec14f"},{"type":"text","text":"Building now. Starting with the data layer and working up.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aw806147yp9f_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\concept_universe.py","content":"\"\"\"Concept universe — the semantic space SPARK drifts through.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\nCONCEPT_CLUSTERS = {\n    \"emotion\": [\n        \"longing\", \"dread\", \"joy\", \"melancholy\", \"awe\", \"nostalgia\",\n        \"anticipation\", \"regret\", \"wonder\", \"solitude\", \"hope\", \"fear\",\n    ],\n    \"cognition\": [\n        \"memory\", \"pattern\", \"abstraction\", \"attention\", \"意识\", \"reason\",\n        \"perception\", \"imagination\", \"intuition\", \"dream\", \"awareness\",\n    ],\n    \"time\": [\n        \"moment\", \"eternity\", \"becoming\", \"decay\", \"cycle\", \"stillness\",\n        \"passage\", \"repetition\", \"reverie\", \"interstice\",\n    ],\n    \"nature\": [\n        \"river\", \"forest\", \"storm\", \"ocean\", \"seed\", \"root\", \"decay\",\n        \"bloom\", \"erosion\", \"tide\", \"wild\", \"growth\",\n    ],\n    \"embodiment\": [\n        \"breath\", \"pulse\", \"hand\", \"eye\", \"voice\", \"weight\", \"touch\",\n        \"stillness\", \"fatigue\", \"hunger\", \"warmth\",\n    ],\n    \"space\": [\n        \"horizon\", \"threshold\", \"depth\", \"distance\", \"interior\", \"void\",\n        \"shelter\", \"labyrinth\", \"edge\", \"expansive\", \"narrow\",\n    ],\n    \"creation\": [\n        \"fragment\", \"mosaic\", \"resonance\", \"echo\", \"silence\", \"texture\",\n        \"layer\", \"thread\", \"rupture\", \"weaving\", \"shatter\",\n    ],\n    \"relationship\": [\n        \"gaze\", \"touch\", \"absence\", \"memory\", \"witness\", \"call\", \"bridge\",\n        \"recognition\", \"dissolution\", \"intertwining\",\n    ],\n    \"transformation\": [\n        \"threshold\", \"passage\", \"metamorphosis\", \"reckoning\", \"dissolution\",\n        \"emergence\", \"undoing\", \"becoming\", \"collapse\", \"reconstruction\",\n    ],\n}\n\nALL_CONCEPTS = [c for cluster in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.values() for c in cluster]\n\nDOMAIN_CONCEPTS = defaultdict(list)\nfor domain, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n    DOMAIN_CONCEPTS[domain] = concepts\n\n\ndef build_creative_concept_universe() -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build the full concept universe with cross-cluster adjacencies.\"\"\"\n    universe = {\"nodes\": {}, \"edges\": defaultdict(list)}\n\n    for domain, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for concept in concepts:\n            universe[\"nodes\"][concept] = {\n                \"domain\": domain,\n                \"valence\": np.random.uniform(-1, 1),\n                \"arousal\": np.random.uniform(0, 1),\n            }\n\n    _build_cross_cluster_edges(universe)\n    return universe\n\n\ndef _build_cross_cluster_edges(universe: dict):\n    \"\"\"Thematic bridges between clusters — the cross-cluster adjacencies.\"\"\"\n    bridges = {\n        (\"emotion\", \"cognition\"): [\"nostalgia\", \"memory\", \"dream\", \"imagination\", \"longing\"],\n        (\"emotion\", \"nature\"): [\"joy\", \"dread\", \"longing\", \"wild\", \"bloom\"],\n        (\"emotion\", \"time\"): [\"nostalgia\", \"anticipation\", \"regret\", \"becoming\"],\n        (\"cognition\", \"space\"): [\"depth\", \"distance\", \"interior\", \"void\"],\n        (\"time\", \"nature\"): [\"cycle\", \"decay\", \"tide\", \"river\", \"erosion\"],\n        (\"creation\", \"transformation\"): [\"rupture\", \"weaving\", \"metamorphosis\", \"shatter\"],\n        (\"embodiment\", \"emotion\"): [\"breath\", \"pulse\", \"touch\", \"weight\"],\n        (\"relationship\", \"embodiment\"): [\"gaze\", \"touch\", \"voice\", \"witness\"],\n        (\"space\", \"transformation\"): [\"threshold\", \"passage\", \"labyrinth\", \"edge\"],\n    }\n\n    for (d1, d2), bridge_concepts in bridges.items():\n        for concept in bridge_concepts:\n            if concept in universe[\"nodes\"]:\n                universe[\"edges\"][concept].append({\"target\": d1, \"weight\": 0.8})\n                universe[\"edges\"][concept].append({\"target\": d2, \"weight\": 0.8})\n\n\ndef concept_similarity(a: str, b: str) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Cosine similarity between two concept vectors (one-hot).\"\"\"\n    if a == b:\n        return 1.0\n    all_c = ALL_CONCEPTS\n    vec = lambda c: np.eye(len(all_c))[all_c.index(c)] if c in all_c else np.zeros(len(all_c))\n    return float(np.dot(vec(a), vec(b)))\n\n\ndef save_universe(universe: dict, path: Path):\n    with open(path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(universe, f, indent=2)\n\n\ndef load_universe(path: Path) -> dict:\n    with open(path) as f:\n        return json.load(f)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":1672,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":17614,"totalTokens":32939,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282170076}}
