{"type":"message","id":"857753cb","parentId":"b1b51d24","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:29.744Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `drift_chamber` directory inside `spark` only has a `__pycache__` with .pyc files - no source .py files and no `__init__.py`. The actual source is in `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\drift_chamber\\`.\n\nSo the engine.py needs to either:\n1. Add the drift-chamber path to sys.path\n2. Or reference it as a separate package\n\nLooking at the bytecode imports: `drift_chamber`, `ConceptGraph`, `ConceptNode`, `DriftChamberConfig`, `drift_cycle`, `decay`\n\n\nIt references `ConceptGraph`, `ConceptNode`, and `DriftChamberConfig` from the drift_chamber package, so I need to check what the actual source files in the drift-chamber directory provide.","thinkingSignature":"e9862e2c8841be26019eca0a05bc6b5ffa28f4f20329ce6ddaf7be35bcbdf9f3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mvwnmzccv4c_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\drift_chamber\\__init__.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mvwnmzccv4c_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\drift_chamber\\config.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20901,"output":274,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34785,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282223244}}
{"type":"message","id":"92daf0c4","parentId":"857753cb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:29.849Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1mvwnmzccv4c_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Drift Chamber\n# Constrained semantic drift as a model of imaginative cognition\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Set\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n__version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n\nfrom .graph import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode\nfrom .operators import diffuse, steer, decay, checkpoint, drift_cycle\nfrom .gap import gap_event\nfrom .metrics import coherence_score, novelty_score, activation_entropy, interpret_drift_regime\nfrom .config import DriftChamberConfig\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774282229807}}
{"type":"message","id":"10ef1a41","parentId":"92daf0c4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:29.885Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1mvwnmzccv4c_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Configuration for Drift Chamber.\"\"\"\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import List, Optional\nimport numpy as np\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass DriftChamberConfig:\n    \"\"\"Configuration for the drift chamber experiment.\"\"\"\n\n    # Diffusion\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.3  # How fast activation spreads per step\n\n    # Steering\n    steering_strength: float = 0.5  # 0 = pure drift, 1 = pure goal pull\n\n    # Decay\n    decay_rate: float = 0.05  # Per-step activation decay\n\n    # Gap (session boundary)\n    gap_decay_rate: float = 0.8  # Multiplicative decay on gap event\n    gap_activation_threshold: float = 0.3  # Min activation to survive gap\n\n    # Checkpointing\n    activation_threshold: float = 0.1  # Min activation to survive step\n    checkpoint_path: str = \"./checkpoints\"\n\n    # Simulation\n    max_steps: int = 100\n    seed: int = 42\n\n    # Embeddings (optional — uses simple random if None)\n    embedding_dim: int = 128\n    use_real_embeddings: bool = False\n\n    def __post_init__(self):\n        assert 0 <= self.diffusion_rate <= 1\n        assert 0 <= self.steering_strength <= 1\n        assert 0 <= self.decay_rate <= 1\n        assert 0 <= self.gap_decay_rate <= 1\n        assert 0 <= self.activation_threshold <= 1\n        assert 0 <= self.gap_activation_threshold <= 1\n\n    def to_dict(self) -> dict:\n        return {\n            'diffusion_rate': self.diffusion_rate,\n            'steering_strength': self.steering_strength,\n            'decay_rate': self.decay_rate,\n            'gap_decay_rate': self.gap_decay_rate,\n            'gap_activation_threshold': self.gap_activation_threshold,\n            'activation_threshold': self.activation_threshold,\n            'max_steps': self.max_steps,\n            'seed': self.seed,\n        }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774282229852}}
{"type":"message","id":"69ff4ebf","parentId":"10ef1a41","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:41.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I can write engine.py that wraps drift_chamber properly, adding the drift-chamber source path to sys.path so the import works.","thinkingSignature":"77c72181089125729b6c0444c05f1cbef4e198100e1eee309c008e77f3601f6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_moratdhf313f_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py","content":"\"\"\"SPARK creative engine — drift chamber + LLM mapped to creative tensions.\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add the real drift-chamber source to path\n_SPARK_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent\n_DRIFT_PATH = _SPARK_DIR.parent / \"drift-chamber\"\nif str(_DRIFT_PATH) not in sys.path:\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(_DRIFT_PATH))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph,\n    ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle,\n    decay,\n)\n\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass SPARKConfig:\n    \"\"\"SPARK engine configuration.\"\"\"\n    steering_strength: float = 0.2  # 0.1-0.3 is the IMAGINATIVE regime\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.3\n    decay_rate: float = 0.05\n    max_steps: int = 20\n    seed: int = 42\n    embedding_dim: int = 128\n\n\ndef build_graph(concept_adj: Dict[str, Dict[str, float]]) -> ConceptGraph:\n    \"\"\"Build a ConceptGraph from adjacency dict.\"\"\"\n    graph = ConceptGraph()\n    for concept, neighbors in concept_adj.items():\n        for neighbor, weight in neighbors.items():\n            graph.add_edge(concept, neighbor, weight)\n    return graph\n\n\ndef run_drift(\n    concept_adj: Dict[str, Dict[str, float]],\n    tensions: List[Tuple[str, str]],\n    config: SPARKConfig,\n    seed_concept: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run a drift cycle through the concept graph.\n    Returns dict with path, activations, regime.\n    \"\"\"\n    drift_cfg = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=config.steering_strength,\n        diffusion_rate=config.diffusion_rate,\n        decay_rate=config.decay_rate,\n        max_steps=config.max_steps,\n        seed=config.seed,\n        embedding_dim=config.embedding_dim,\n    )\n\n    graph = build_graph(concept_adj)\n\n    if seed_concept and seed_concept in concept_adj:\n        graph.activate([seed_concept], [1.0])\n\n    path, activations = drift_cycle(graph, tensions, drift_cfg)\n    return {\n        \"path\": path,\n        \"activations\": activations,\n        \"config\": drift_cfg.to_dict(),\n    }\n\n\ndef get_drift_path(\n    concept_adj: Dict[str, Dict[str, float]],\n    tensions: List[Tuple[str, str]],\n    config: SPARKConfig,\n    seed_concept: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"Get just the concept path from a drift run.\"\"\"\n    result = run_drift(concept_adj, tensions, config, seed_concept)\n    return result[\"path\"]\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21746,"output":670,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36026,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282229887}}
