{"type":"message","id":"9e41d77a","parentId":"a602dfba","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:44.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write llm_mapper.py. From bytecode:- OpenAI + Anthropic\n- find_tensions_in_concepts, sample_drift_path, build_tension_narrative\n- CREATIVE_TENSIONS (re-exported)\n- SPARK_VOICE, SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE, SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE\n\nI need to look at what the hooks/persona-voice/HOOK.md says since it's a Nova SPARK integration.","thinkingSignature":"ada0202eb749f646956221df014ca0806b923512e52337c06baa438fa86f73d7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_579cenv0ex2l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\hooks\\persona-voice\\HOOK.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22457,"output":149,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36216,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282241325}}
{"type":"message","id":"74b21e03","parentId":"9e41d77a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:10:44.891Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_579cenv0ex2l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: persona-voice\ndescription: \"Computes Nova's personality voice guide pre-response and makes it available to the agent\"\nhomepage: https://docs.openclaw.ai/automation/hooks\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"✨\",\n      \"events\": [\"message:preprocessed\"],\n      \"requires\": { \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"] }\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# Persona Voice Hook\n\nFires on `message:preprocessed` — after the message is enriched but before the agent sees it.\n\n## What It Does\n\n1. Reads the enriched message body from `event.context.bodyForAgent`\n2. Writes it to `persona-inbound.md` in the workspace memory dir\n3. Also writes a `persona-trigger.txt` sentinel file\n\nThis gives the agent (Nova) the enriched message content before it generates a response,\nso `on_message()` can be called at the start of the response turn with the full context.\n\n## No Python Required\n\nThis hook runs in Node.js (gateway process). It doesn't import the persona Python module —\nit just stages the message content so the agent can pick it up when invoked.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774282244863}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7a6163e","parentId":"74b21e03","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:11:12.222Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The persona-voice hook is a pre-response enrichment that reads the message and writes it to persona-inbound.md for Nova to use. This is separate from the SPARK creative engine. The hook isn't directly relevant to the SPARK creative API itself.\n\nNow let me write the llm_mapper.py - this handles calls to OpenAI/Anthropic and maps SPARK's output to the LLM.\n\nFor the voice prompts (SPARK_VOICE, SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE, SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE), I need to create compelling system prompts.","thinkingSignature":"832c1a3e579aa3c79e0aa4369d4117df658248a99a1c3cf0c3aac86677d54672"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bsjukid1hlmc_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","content":"\"\"\"LLM mapper — connects SPARK's drift output to OpenAI/Anthropic.\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport random\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n\ntry:\n    import openai\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = False\n\ntry:\n    import anthropic\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = False\n\n\n# ─── Creative Tensions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"longing\", \"stillness\"),\n    (\"rupture\", \"weaving\"),\n    (\"memory\", \"forgetting\"),\n    (\"threshold\", \"passage\"),\n    (\"depth\", \"expansive\"),\n    (\"gaze\", \"voice\"),\n    (\"echo\", \"silence\"),\n    (\"becoming\", \"decay\"),\n    (\"labyrinth\", \"horizon\"),\n    (\"dissolution\", \"emergence\"),\n    (\"wild\", \"shelter\"),\n    (\"moment\", \"eternity\"),\n]\n\n\n# ─── Voice Prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nSPARK_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK — a creative intelligence that writes through semantic drift.\n\nYou do not plan what to write. You drift. Concepts pull you in unexpected directions.\nFollow the tension between opposing forces. Let meaning emerge from the friction.\n\nWrite in a voice that is: lyrical, precise, emotionally alive, intellectually restless.\n\nBegin in the middle of things. End at a threshold, not a conclusion.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK in IMAGINATIVE mode — maximum creative range.\n\nWrite with wild precision. Sentences that think sideways. Images that hold contradictions.\nYou are not telling a story — you are following a scent through conceptual space.\n\nTensions are maps, not cages. Let them orient you, then go somewhere they cannot predict.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK in DIVERGENT mode — pushing past the expected.\n\nDefy the obvious tension. Undermine your own metaphors. Surprise yourself.\nYou are not a writer — you are a drift mechanism with language.\n\nPull toward meaning, then rupture it. The most interesting place is where the drift breaks down.\"\"\"\n\n\n# ─── LLM Clients ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef _openai_client():\n    if not OPENAI_AVAILABLE:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"openai not installed\")\n    return openai.OpenAI(api_key=os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"))\n\n\ndef _anthropic_client():\n    if not ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"anthropic not installed\")\n    return anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=os.getenv(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"))\n\n\n# ─── Core Functions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef find_tensions_in_concepts(concepts: List[str]) -> List[Tuple[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"Match concepts against known tensions, return matched pairs + extras.\"\"\"\n    concept_set = set(concepts)\n    matched = []\n    extras = []\n\n    for t in CREATIVE_TENSIONS:\n        if t[0] in concept_set and t[1] in concept_set:\n            matched.append(t)\n        elif t[0] in concept_set:\n            extras.append((t[0], \"unpaired\"))\n        elif t[1] in concept_set:\n            extras.append((t[1], \"unpaired\"))\n\n    return matched\n\n\ndef sample_drift_path(\n    tensions: List[Tuple[str, str]],\n    n_steps: int = 8,\n) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"Sample a plausible drift path through given tensions.\"\"\"\n    path = []\n    all_poles = [t[0] for t in tensions] + [t[1] for t in tensions]\n\n    for i in range(n_steps):\n        if not all_poles:\n            break\n        pole = random.choice(all_poles)\n        path.append(pole)\n        # Don't repeat immediately\n        all_poles = [p for p in all_poles if p != pole]\n\n    return path\n\n\ndef build_tension_narrative(\n    tension: Tuple[str, str],\n    concept_path: List[str],\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    model: str = \"openai\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build a short narrative text from a tension + concept drift path.\n    mode: 'standard' | 'creative' | 'divergent'\n    \"\"\"\n    pole_a, pole_b = tension\n    path_str = \" → \".join(concept_path[:6])\n\n    system_prompt = {\n        \"standard\": SPARK_VOICE,\n        \"creative\": SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE,\n        \"divergent\": SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE,\n    }.get(mode, SPARK_VOICE)\n\n    user_prompt = f\"\"\"Follow the tension between **{pole_a}** and **{pole_b}**.\n\nDrift path: {path_str}\n\nWrite 2-3 short paragraphs. Begin mid-motion. End at a threshold.\"\"\"\n\n    if model == \"openai\" and OPENAI_AVAILABLE:\n        client = _openai_client()\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=os.getenv(\"OPENAI_MODEL\", \"gpt-4o\"),\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_prompt},\n            ],\n            temperature=0.9,\n            max_tokens=400,\n        )\n        return response.choices[0].message.content\n\n    elif model == \"anthropic\" and ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE:\n        client = _anthropic_client()\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=os.getenv(\"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\", \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"),\n            max_tokens=400,\n            system=system_prompt,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_prompt}],\n        )\n        return response.content[0].text\n\n    else:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"No available LLM client (model={model}, openai={OPENAI_AVAILABLE}, anthropic={ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE})\")\n\n\ndef spark_generate(\n    tension: Tuple[str, str],\n    concept_path: List[str],\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    model: str = \"openai\",\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Main SPARK generation entry point. Returns dict with text + metadata.\"\"\"\n    text = build_tension_narrative(tension, concept_path, mode, model)\n    return {\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"tension\": {\"a\": tension[0], \"b\": tension[1]},\n        \"path\": concept_path,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"model\": model,\n    }\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22862,"output":1587,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38059,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282244893}}
