{"type":"message","id":"ca7ae083","parentId":"45baebb5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:15:03.724Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the path fix worked. Now the error is that there's no OpenAI API key set. This is expected since we don't have one in this environment. The flow is working correctly:\n1. Rate limiting passes\n2. Drift path generation works\n3. LLM call fails because no API key\n\nThis is the correct behavior. Let me add a \"demo mode\" that returns the path and a placeholder text when no API key is available, so the API can be tested end-to-end without the LLM.\n\nBut actually, let me first just verify the path is being returned correctly by adding a fallback. Let me also add better error handling for the no-API-key case.","thinkingSignature":"347acab5d22a9b02fce3c7e4b4ada2fcf846b328f625a15186133509c456c902"},{"type":"text","text":"API key not set — that's expected. The drift path is working, the failure is only at the LLM call. Let me add a demo mode fallback so the full pipeline works without credentials:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vzrix1p1tpkj_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","old_string":"def spark_generate(\n    tension: Tuple[str, str],\n    concept_path: List[str],\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    model: str = \"openai\",\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Main SPARK generation entry point. Returns dict with text + metadata.\"\"\"\n    text = build_tension_narrative(tension, concept_path, mode, model)\n    return {\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"tension\": {\"a\": tension[0], \"b\": tension[1]},\n        \"path\": concept_path,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"model\": model,\n    }","new_string":"def spark_generate(\n    tension: Tuple[str, str],\n    concept_path: List[str],\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    model: str = \"openai\",\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Main SPARK generation entry point. Returns dict with text + metadata.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        text = build_tension_narrative(tension, concept_path, mode, model)\n    except RuntimeError as e:\n        if \"api_key\" in str(e) or \"No available LLM\" in str(e):\n            # Demo mode — return path without LLM call\n            text = _demo_text(tension, concept_path, mode)\n        else:\n            raise\n    return {\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"tension\": {\"a\": tension[0], \"b\": tension[1]},\n        \"path\": concept_path,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"model\": model,\n    }\n\n\ndef _demo_text(tension: Tuple[str, str], path: List[str], mode: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Placeholder text when no LLM is available.\"\"\"\n    modes = {\n        \"standard\": \"Drifting through\",\n        \"creative\": \"Imaginative exploration of\",\n        \"divergent\": \"Breaking from\",\n    }\n    prefix = modes.get(mode, \"Exploring\")\n    path_str = \" → \".join(path[:6])\n    return (\n        f\"[{prefix.upper()} MODE — DEMO OUTPUT]\\n\\n\"\n        f\"Tension: {tension[0]} ↔ {tension[1]}\\n\"\n        f\"Drift path: {path_str}\\n\\n\"\n        f\"The tension between **{tension[0]}** and **{tension[1]}** pulls the narrative apart. \"\n        f\"Without an LLM call, this is where the semantic resonance would become prose. \"\n        f\"Set OPENAI_API_KEY or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY to see the full generation.\"\n    )"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38832,"output":774,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53216,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774282485885}}
