{"type":"message","id":"bb9a7fca","parentId":"e244c20b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:43:15.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking where to put his OpenAI API key. The cleanest way on Windows is to set it as an environment variable, which the uvicorn session will pick up.","thinkingSignature":"51232ba90a4915a3ef278357ff2b4c1cfe5fbd5ad8408827ff2ce1815ecf8eef"},{"type":"text","text":"You can set it in that terminal where the server is running:\n\n```\nsetx OPENAI_API_KEY your_key_here\n```\n\nThen restart the server (Ctrl+C in that terminal, then run `python -m uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8099`).\n\nOr permanently via system environment variables — Win+R → `sysdm.cpl` → Advanced → Environment Variables → User variables → New → `OPENAI_API_KEY` = your key.\n\nAfter setting, make sure you restart the server in that terminal window for it to pick up the variable."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":167,"cacheRead":68530,"cacheWrite":152,"totalTokens":68892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774284188422}}
