{"type":"message","id":"b024059e","parentId":"b0a8ef27","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:50:32.536Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to know how to use the SPARK API now. Let me give him a quick overview of the endpoints and how to call them.","thinkingSignature":"94bb4c54c79701f7e6bc21dd8c27c9d5bb49498f232eda822a0552d6e7a6b52d"},{"type":"text","text":"In that terminal window where the server is running, you can hit it a few ways:\n\n**Try it in the terminal with curl:**\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8099/creative/generate ^\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" ^\n  -d \"{\\\"tension_a\\\":\\\"longing\\\",\\\"tension_b\\\":\\\"stillness\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"creative\\\",\\\"n_steps\\\":8}\"\n```\n\n**Or open the docs in your browser:**\n```\nhttp://localhost:8099/docs\n```\nThen click POST /creative/generate → Try it out → fill in the fields → Execute.\n\n**Endpoints:**\n| Method | Path | What it does |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health` | Health check |\n| GET | `/creative/tensions` | List all 12 tensions |\n| POST | `/creative/generate` | Generate text from a tension |\n| POST | `/creative/expand` | Expand previous output |\n| GET | `/plans` | Rate limit info |\n\n**Params for `/generate`:**\n- `tension_a` / `tension_b` — the two poles (e.g. \"longing\" ↔ \"stillness\")\n- `mode` — `standard` | `creative` | `divergent`\n- `n_steps` — drift path length (3–20)\n- `model` — `openai` (or `anthropic` if you set that key too)\n\nWhat tension do you want to try?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":337,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":64625,"totalTokens":69251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774284620625}}
{"type":"message","id":"6fbb63c2","parentId":"b024059e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:54:31.998Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 12:54 EDT] seed concept?"}],"timestamp":1774284871992}}
{"type":"message","id":"d30fc0ef","parentId":"6fbb63c2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:54:38.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about the seed_concept parameter - what it does and whether to use it.","thinkingSignature":"6f09428e91ce6e7c75683a520927b3eb48d7c31718784cc537b91dfc24241c42"},{"type":"text","text":"`seed_concept` is optional — it anchors the drift path to a specific starting concept from the universe. If you leave it out, it just picks one randomly from the graph.\n\nIt's useful if you want the generation to start from a specific thematic direction. Otherwise the engine just picks a concept that connects to your tension poles and drifts outward from there.\n\nFor most cases you can ignore it and just use `tension_a` + `tension_b`. Want to just try a tension without it?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":125,"cacheRead":68854,"cacheWrite":380,"totalTokens":69402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774284871996}}
