{"type":"message","id":"9b6c4fc1","parentId":"cc50338d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:12:30.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the API is returning \"strings of random\" - not a readable story. This suggests the LLM call might be working (since they're getting text back), but the quality is poor. Let me look at what could be going wrong.\n\nLet me think about what might be happening:\n1. The LLM call is succeeding (since they're getting text back)\n2. But the output is \"random strings\" or gibberish\n\nThis could be a few things:\n1. The prompt itself might be malformed\n2. The model being used might not be right\n3. Temperature might be too high\n4. The concept path strings might be leaking into the prompt in a weird way\n\n\n5. The system prompt could be overriding the character's voice, or there's an encoding issue with how the concept path is being formatted\n\nLet me check the actual output to see what's being returned, and then look at the llm_mapper code to trace where the prompt is being constructed and how the concept path is being inserted.","thinkingSignature":"82b206bbaf704de18b617c8e3aaa4e9e55b9e1b2de02da2f6856d174cb93b548"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check what it's actually returning:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6s8nob1g15j0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark; python -c \"\nimport http.client, json, os\nos.environ['PYTHONIOENCODING'] = 'utf-8'\nconn = http.client.HTTPConnection('127.0.0.1', 8099, timeout=15)\nbody = json.dumps({'tension_a': 'longing', 'tension_b': 'stillness', 'mode': 'creative', 'model': 'openai', 'n_steps': 6})\nheaders = {'Content-Type': 'application/json'}\nconn.request('POST', '/creative/generate', body=body, headers=headers)\nresp = conn.getresponse()\ndata = json.loads(resp.read().decode())\nprint('Status:', resp.status)\nprint('Path:', data['path'])\nprint('Text:', data['text'])\n\" 2>&1","timeout":20}