{"type":"message","id":"ba42939c","parentId":"2bf395e4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:36:06.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem. The text still shows the demo output and the path still has ConceptNode objects (not strings). The server that's running is still the OLD code. Even though the server process shows it's running and responding to requests, it seems like it's using the OLD code.\n\nThis is because when I run `Start-Process` to start the server in a new terminal, that terminal's `python` is not necessarily the same Python environment that has the edited source files. Or more likely, the new terminal window is starting the server from a different directory or the Python environment there is not picking up the new code.\n\nWait, actually - the `spark_output.json` was created by the CURRENT server (port 8099), and it still shows the ConceptNode issue. \n\nThe demo text and ConceptNode path mean the server is still running the old code with the buggy conversion logic. But I've been editing the source files directly in `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py` - so why isn't the server picking up the changes? When I started it with `Start-Process` in the new terminal, something must have gone wrong with how it loaded the code.\n\nActually, I think I see it now - `Start-Process` opens a new terminal window with its own environment, and that terminal probably started the server with the old compiled `.pyc` files still cached. The server would need a restart to pick up my edits. But more likely, my current Python process that's making test requests is using a different environment entirely, which is why it's not seeing the changes.\n\nWait, the real problem is simpler - when `Start-Process` launches the new terminal, it's starting fresh without loading the user's profile, so any environment variables set at the system level won't be available there. That's why the new terminal can't find what it needs.","thinkingSignature":"afa53ab6358b1097b08cd91ae4e1f1e63698e3149d97389f3fe1b08e1b1dfbf7"},{"type":"text","text":"The server in that terminal is still running the old code. The new terminal window doesn't inherit the current process's environment changes. You need to manually restart it in that terminal. \n\nIn that terminal window, type:\n```\nCtrl+C\npython -m uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8099\n```\n\nThe server there was started before the API key fix was compiled. This terminal is fresh — the cmd.exe process `Start-Process` creates starts with the system environment as it exists right now, but the Python process it runs is loading whatever `.pyc` files were compiled at that moment. Since the ConceptNode fix was edited into source files but the server hadn't restarted, it's still running stale bytecode.\n\nOr if you want me to just test it from here without the terminal — I can hit it directly. Want me to do that and show you what a real generation looks like?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":132842,"output":577,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147029,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774287348880}}
