{"type":"message","id":"5d5bdd53","parentId":"f65a7c06","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:37:40.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about coding plans/services that are under $10/month with good usage amounts. This is a general question about AI coding tools, not specifically about SPARK. Let me think about what options are available:\n\n1. **OpenAI API** - Pay-as-you-go, not a subscription. GPT-4o is expensive per token, GPT-4o-mini is cheap. Not really a \"plan\" under $10 fixed.\n\n2. **GitHub Copilot** - $10/month for individuals (Copilot Individual). Good for coding autocomplete. Has a free tier for students/OSS maintainers.\n\n\n3. **Cursor** - Free tier available, Pro plan is $20/month, so that's out. **Claude** through Anthropic's API is pay-as-you-go rather than a fixed plan, with Claude 3.5 Sonnet being quite affordable. **GitHub Copilot** is the main $10/month option that fits the criteria. **Codex** through OpenAI and **Cody** by Sourcegraph are alternatives, though Cody's pricing isn't clearly specified. There are probably other options worth considering too.\n\n4. **Tabnine** - Free tier available, Pro around $10/month, though it seems more basic than Copilot. **Amazon CodeWhisperer** - Free for individuals. **Replit** - Has paid plans but they're fairly priced. **LemCal** and similar tools are also available in this space.","thinkingSignature":"e87f2b9cc0cdafe6d1d705e8d81ceaaf32d41202f19761894127e8c3c6468036"},{"type":"text","text":"Quick search for what's actually good value under $10/mo for coding:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9e4lsyrs8qsu_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"best AI coding tools subscription under $10 per month 2026","count":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":359,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":132939,"totalTokens":146951,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774287446478}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd2798c0","parentId":"5d5bdd53","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:37:40.544Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9e4lsyrs8qsu_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"error\": \"missing_brave_api_key\",\n  \"message\": \"web_search (brave) needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web\"\n}"}],"details":{"error":"missing_brave_api_key","message":"web_search (brave) needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.","docs":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774287460507}}
{"type":"message","id":"93130013","parentId":"cd2798c0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:37:54.028Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No web search available. Let me just answer from knowledge.\n\nThe main options I know of:\n\n1. **GitHub Copilot** - $10/month — the industry standard, works in VS Code, JetBrains, etc. Very good value.\n\n2. **Cursor** - Free tier available. Pro is $20/mo. Not under $10.\n\n3. **Cody (Sourcegraph)** - Free tier, Pro $9/mo (or was $10?). Not sure about current pricing.\n\n4. **Tabnine** - Free tier, Pro ~$10/mo. More lightweight than Copilot.\n\n\n5. **Amazon CodeWhisperer** - Completely free for individual developers.\n\n6. **Replit** - Offers a free tier with paid plans that are quite reasonable.\n\n7. **ChatGPT Team** - $20/user/mo, so that's out of range.\n\n8. **Devin (Cognition)** - No pricing announced yet.\n\nFor someone who wants to code and ship, **GitHub Copilot** is probably the strongest choice at $10/month since it integrates directly into the IDE and works well for autocomplete and code generation.\n\n**Tabnine** is the more budget-friendly option at roughly $10/mo with a solid autocomplete experience and privacy-focused features. **Cody** has potential but the pricing isn't as clear. **Amazon CodeWhisperer** stands out as completely free if they don't mind using AWS tooling.","thinkingSignature":"7f633639569d2c3f0d9437b1db7bb4ed532bc0c1e9c74598fdcbf83224bf5657"},{"type":"text","text":"From what I know (no web search right now):\n\n**Best actual $10/mo options:**\n\n- **GitHub Copilot** — $10/month. Industry standard, works in VS Code/JetBrains/Neovim. Great completions + can do whole functions. Best bang for buck if you're actively coding.\n\n- **Tabnine** — ~$10/month. Lighter weight, very fast completions. Less feature-rich than Copilot but privacy-respecting (enterprise-trained model, your code stays private).\n\n- **Cody (Sourcegraph)** — not sure on current pricing but was competitive. Good for代码 search + autocomplete across large codebases.\n\n**Free options worth knowing:**\n- **Amazon CodeWhisperer** — free for individuals, surprisingly decent\n- **Cursor free tier** — limited but usable\n- **Continue.dev** — free, self-hostable with local models\n\nFor your use case (rapid iteration, shipping fast, lots of simultaneous projects) — GitHub Copilot at $10 is probably the most practical. Tabnine if you care about code privacy.\n\nWhat's the main thing you're trying to do — autocomplete, agent-style pair programming, or something else?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":133424,"output":536,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774287460549}}
