{"type":"message","id":"158f1902","parentId":"2399d4a2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:41:54.177Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about cheap/minimal cost AI APIs that give API keys with free/daily limits - like MiniMax (which he's already using), or similar services. He's probably looking for alternatives to OpenAI for the SPARK API that won't cost much or have free tiers.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n\n- **MiniMax** - he's already using it (model: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7) via the OpenClaw gateway. Not sure about direct API access pricing.\n- **Groq** - has a free tier with rate limits, extremely fast inference\n- **Together AI** - has free tier, many open models\n\n\n- **Anthropic** - $3-15/month for API access, not free\n- **Google AI** (Gemini) - has a free tier with limits\n- **Replicate** - pay-per-use, very cheap for small runs\n- **Perplexity API** - has free tier\n- **Cohere** - has free tier\n- **OpenRouter** - unified API to many models, some free, cheap options\n- **Hugging Face Inference API** - free tier for many models\n\nMost of these either have free tiers with daily limits or pay-per-use models that work out cheaper depending on usage patterns.\n\nSince he's already on MiniMax through OpenClaw, I should focus on which other services he's likely already using or could easily access - Groq and OpenRouter stand out as the most practical for API-first workflows.","thinkingSignature":"5ebb7400c7c0120733103c39a0a8cfed05916804d0349bced924f154b9e526ad"},{"type":"text","text":"Ah, like free-tier API providers with daily credits. A few:\n\n- **Groq** — free tier, fast inference on Llama/Mixtral. Daily rate limits but quite generous. Good for open models.\n\n- **OpenRouter** — unified API, some models have free daily credits. Routes to Groq, Together, Anyscale, etc. One key, many backends.\n\n- **Together AI** — $5 free credits/month, then pay-per-token. Good for fine-tuned stuff.\n\n- **Cohere** — free tier, 5M tokens/month on the trial. Good embeddings + command models.\n\n- **Replicate** — pay-per-run, not per month. Super cheap for small volumes.\n\n- **Google Gemini** — free tier, some quota. Good as a fallback.\n\nFor SPARK specifically, since it only needs short bursts of text generation, any of these would work. Groq or OpenRouter would be the easiest to plug in — just swap the API base URL and key in `llm_mapper.py`.\n\nWant me to add Groq as an option?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":538,"cacheRead":146991,"cacheWrite":15,"totalTokens":147587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774287698268}}
