{"type":"message","id":"dcacddb7","parentId":"e4362208","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:51:47.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, this still won't work because the environment variable set via PowerShell `$env:` only persists in the current shell session. When I background it with `exec`, the child process inherits the current environment including GROQ_API_KEY.\n\nActually wait - when I use `exec` with `background=true`, the process is spawned as a background process inheriting the current process's environment variables. Since I set `$env:GROQ_API_KEY` in the same command, the child process should inherit it.\n\nBut wait - `$env:VAR = value` in PowerShell sets the environment variable for the current process ONLY. When I then call `python` with `&`, the child python process inherits those environment variables. And when I background it with `background=true`, the background process also inherits them.","thinkingSignature":"8ec0251e0c711741fed1a5fa80725853f18382a1bc9a3755c8499af0e7a91f22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3egirdwi7ssg_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"brisk-trail","timeout":8000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":129775,"output":212,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143597,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288300382}}
