{"type":"message","id":"15fe4768","parentId":"538efb3f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:31.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `data['path']` contains ANSI escape codes (the `[31;1m` prefix). That's because `get_drift_path` returns strings, but the path elements actually contain ANSI escape codes from the console output. The ConceptNode fix I made converts the ConceptNode to its string representation via `str()`, which on Windows includes ANSI escape codes for colors.\n\nLooking at the error message: `[31;1mTraceback (most recent call last):[0m` - this is ANSI colored output from the ConceptNode.__repr__ that was captured when the error occurred. Wait no - the ConceptNode itself was converted to a string using `str()`. \n\nI'm realizing the issue is that `hasattr(n, \"name\")` is checking for a `.name` attribute, but the actual attribute on ConceptNode is `.id` - so that condition fails and we fall through to `str(n)`, which in Windows PTY mode with color support captures the ANSI escape sequences. I need to check what the actual attribute name is in the ConceptNode class to fix this properly.","thinkingSignature":"1cb9149eabf2830e0143d79962d1df1c443ebd7a17fdc008c937ac2825282e5c"},{"type":"text","text":"The path strings contain ANSI color codes from Windows terminal. Let me check what attribute the ConceptNode uses:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_20ir7vmsf1af_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\drift_chamber\\__init__.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119281,"output":294,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133185,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288403234}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8670513","parentId":"15fe4768","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:31.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_20ir7vmsf1af_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Drift Chamber\n# Constrained semantic drift as a model of imaginative cognition\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Set\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n__version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n\nfrom .graph import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode\nfrom .operators import diffuse, steer, decay, checkpoint, drift_cycle\nfrom .gap import gap_event\nfrom .metrics import coherence_score, novelty_score, activation_entropy, interpret_drift_regime\nfrom .config import DriftChamberConfig\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288411121}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a4547db","parentId":"a8670513","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:34.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to check the ConceptNode class to see what its actual attribute is.","thinkingSignature":"53f4de81ef9290fafee04b21ffb5f6cac679cde8b607467c63eff29c085f1fe2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7i09ytrbyd9i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\drift_chamber\\graph.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119706,"output":66,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133382,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288411142}}
{"type":"message","id":"79941a3e","parentId":"8a4547db","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:34.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7i09ytrbyd9i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Concept graph data structure for drift chamber.\"\"\"\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Set\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ConceptNode:\n    \"\"\"A node in the concept graph.\"\"\"\n\n    id: str\n    activation: float = 1.0  # Current activation level\n    embedding: Optional[np.ndarray] = None  # Semantic embedding\n    neighbors: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=dict)  # neighbor_id -> edge_weight\n    metadata: dict = field(default_factory=dict)\n    last_updated: int = 0  # Step number\n\n    def add_neighbor(self, neighbor_id: str, weight: float = 1.0):\n        \"\"\"Add a weighted edge to another node.\"\"\"\n        self.neighbors[neighbor_id] = weight\n\n    def cosine_sim(self, other: 'ConceptNode') -> float:\n        \"\"\"Cosine similarity between two nodes.\"\"\"\n        if self.embedding is None or other.embedding is None:\n            return 0.0\n        a = self.embedding.flatten()\n        b = other.embedding.flatten()\n        norm_a = np.linalg.norm(a)\n        norm_b = np.linalg.norm(b)\n        if norm_a == 0 or norm_b == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return float(np.dot(a, b) / (norm_a * norm_b))\n\n\nclass ConceptGraph:\n    \"\"\"A graph of concept nodes with activation dynamics.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, seed: int = 42):\n        self.nodes: Dict[str, ConceptNode] = {}\n        self.current_step: int = 0\n        self._rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n\n    def add_node(self, node: ConceptNode):\n        \"\"\"Add a concept node to the graph.\"\"\"\n        self.nodes[node.id] = node\n\n    def add_edge(self, from_id: str, to_id: str, weight: float = 1.0):\n        \"\"\"Add a directed edge between nodes. Creates nodes if they don't exist.\"\"\"\n        if from_id not in self.nodes:\n            self.add_node(ConceptNode(id=from_id))\n        if to_id not in self.nodes:\n            self.add_node(ConceptNode(id=to_id))\n        self.nodes[from_id].add_neighbor(to_id, weight)\n\n    def add_undirected_edge(self, id1: str, id2: str, weight: float = 1.0):\n        \"\"\"Add bidirectional edges between two nodes.\"\"\"\n        self.add_edge(id1, id2, weight)\n        self.add_edge(id2, id1, weight)\n\n    def get_activations(self) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get array of activations in node order.\"\"\"\n        return np.array([n.activation for n in self.nodes.values()])\n\n    def set_activations(self, activations: np.ndarray):\n        \"\"\"Set activations from array in node order.\"\"\"\n        for i, node in enumerate(self.nodes.values()):\n            node.activation = float(activations[i])\n\n    def get_activation_dict(self) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Get activations as dict.\"\"\"\n        return {node.id: node.activation for node in self.nodes.values()}\n\n    def get_strong_nodes(self, threshold: float) -> List[ConceptNode]:\n        \"\"\"Get nodes with activation above threshold.\"\"\"\n        return [n for n in self.nodes.values() if n.activation >= threshold]\n\n    def prune_weak(self, threshold: float) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove nodes below activation threshold. Returns count removed.\"\"\"\n        to_remove = [nid for nid, n in self.nodes.items() if n.activation < threshold]\n        for nid in to_remove:\n            del self.nodes[nid]\n        return len(to_remove)\n\n    def clone(self) -> 'ConceptGraph':\n        \"\"\"Clone the graph (deep copy of nodes).\"\"\"\n        g = ConceptGraph()\n        g.current_step = self.current_step\n        g.nodes = {k: ConceptNode(\n            id=n.id,\n            activation=n.activation,\n            embedding=n.embedding.copy() if n.embedding is not None else None,\n            neighbors=dict(n.neighbors),\n            metadata=dict(n.metadata),\n            last_updated=n.last_updated,\n        ) for k, n in self.nodes.items()}\n        return g\n\n    def summary(self) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Get a summary dict of the graph state.\"\"\"\n        activations = self.get_activations()\n        return {\n            'step': self.current_step,\n            'num_nodes': len(self.nodes),\n            'mean_activation': float(np.mean(activations)) if len(activations) > 0 else 0.0,\n            'max_activation': float(np.max(activations)) if len(activations) > 0 else 0.0,\n            'min_activation': float(np.min(activations)) if len(activations) > 0 else 0.0,\n            'total_activation': float(np.sum(activations)),\n            'strong_nodes': len(self.get_strong_nodes(0.3)),\n        }\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_seed_concepts(\n        cls,\n        seed_concepts: List[str],\n        embedding_dim: int = 128,\n        seed: int = 42,\n        connect_density: float = 0.3,\n    ) -> 'ConceptGraph':\n        \"\"\"Create a graph from seed concept names.\n\n        Args:\n            seed_concepts: List of concept name strings\n            embedding_dim: Dimension of random embeddings\n            seed: Random seed\n            connect_density: Probability of edge between any two nodes\n        \"\"\"\n        rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n        graph = cls(seed=seed)\n\n        # Create nodes with random embeddings\n        for concept in seed_concepts:\n            node = ConceptNode(\n                id=concept,\n                activation=rng.uniform(0.5, 1.0),\n                embedding=rng.standard_normal(embedding_dim),\n            )\n            graph.add_node(node)\n\n        # Create random edges\n        concepts = list(graph.nodes.keys())\n        for i, c1 in enumerate(concepts):\n            for j, c2 in enumerate(concepts):\n                if i != j and rng.random() < connect_density:\n                    weight = rng.uniform(0.1, 1.0)\n                    graph.add_edge(c1, c2, weight)\n\n        return graph\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288414972}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc251410","parentId":"79941a3e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:42.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the ConceptNode has `id` as its identifier attribute, not `name`. My fix uses `hasattr(n, \"name\")` but it should be `hasattr(n, \"id\")`. Let me fix the `engine.py` get_drift_path function.","thinkingSignature":"0696f6a79e25ebf956334260297e0999da4e98c5438a0def49581aa036cc830c"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it — the attribute is `id`, not `name`. Quick fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxyaay0uxt0q_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py","old_string":"    path = result[\"path\"]\n    # Convert ConceptNode objects to string names\n    return [n.name if hasattr(n, \"name\") else str(n) for n in path]","new_string":"    path = result[\"path\"]\n    # Convert ConceptNode objects to string names\n    return [n.id if hasattr(n, \"id\") else str(n) for n in path]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":121100,"output":212,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134922,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288414990}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a394d90","parentId":"fc251410","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:42.635Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bxyaay0uxt0q_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 82     \"\"\"Get just the concept path (as strings) from a drift run.\"\"\"\n 83     result = run_drift(concept_adj, tensions, config, seed_concept)\n 84     path = result[\"path\"]\n 85     # Convert ConceptNode objects to string names\n-86     return [n.name if hasattr(n, \"name\") else str(n) for n in path]\n+86     return [n.id if hasattr(n, \"id\") else str(n) for n in path]","firstChangedLine":86},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288422620}}
