{"type":"message","id":"afbe9e39","parentId":"7fe4957a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:54:24.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still showing ANSI codes. The server started before the edit took effect because the process was backgrounded. Let me check the `drift_cycle` function in drift-chamber to see what it actually returns as the path. The ANSI codes are coming from somewhere.\n\nActually wait - the `data['path']` still contains ANSI codes. This means `drift_cycle` in drift-chamber returns the path as ConceptNode objects, which my `get_drift_path` converts using `n.id if hasattr(n, \"id\")`. The `n.id` should return the string id (e.g., \"longing\"), not the full object representation.\n \nAh, I see the issue now - I checked the server logs and the `get_drift_path` function is returning the full ConceptNode repr with ANSI color codes, not just the id. So the conversion isn't working as expected. The PTY mode is wrapping `__repr__` with ANSI color codes, so when my fix calls `str(node)`, it gets the color-coded output instead of just the id string. I need to access `node.id` directly to bypass the repr entirely.","thinkingSignature":"13cd85635d9a1146d76bf2aef8b5dcda105d6deb8e044b8807021ce2c55787ca"},{"type":"text","text":"Still ANSI codes — the PTY is wrapping `__repr__` with colors. Need to access `.id` directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_twhkqtcngp0g_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py","old_string":"    path = result[\"path\"]\n    # Convert ConceptNode objects to string names\n    return [n.id if hasattr(n, \"id\") else str(n) for n in path]","new_string":"    path = result[\"path\"]\n    # Convert ConceptNode objects to string names — access .id directly to avoid PTY-wrapped __repr__\n    return [getattr(n, \"id\", str(n)) for n in path]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":122260