{"type":"message","id":"cfc9c071","parentId":"6c87ac59","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:55:15.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `print('PATH:', data['path'])` itself is the problem, not the `data['path']` when I write it to JSON. When I write the path to JSON and then read it back, the data is fine. The issue is that even though `data['path'][:3]` printed fine as `['longing', 'dread', 'joy']`, when I try to print the full list it has Unicode characters that cp1252 can't encode.\n\nLet me just read the text from the file without printing the path.","thinkingSignature":"95ff262171df4d81460ec783e030c9c4daea21aaa0384b9048eb72c0f7b6da51"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mg6ylxj7ge0l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('spark_final2.json', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n# Write story to separate file to avoid encoding issues\nwith open('story.txt', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    f.write(data['text'])\nprint('done')\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":124274,"output":216,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138100,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288509081}}
